This slice corrects a layering mistake.

Relevant existing notes already said this:
- `Tool vs project: clear separation`
- `doctor: facts only, no opinions`
- `Agent onboarding gap: workflow not obvious`

Applied rule:
- user-facing surfaces (`mycelium.sh`, `README.md`, `SKILL.md`, `prime`, `doctor`, shipped examples) should describe the tool and its user experience
- maintainer-facing workflow should live in contributor docs, tests, branch notes, and maintainer process

Changes in this slice:
- renamed `AGENT_CI.md` to `DEVELOPING.md`
- removed the checklist from `prime`
- removed checklist mentions from `README.md` and `SKILL.md`
- removed the maintainer reminder from the example hook
- kept the contributor checklist as a checked-in repo-maintainer doc instead

Validation:
- `./test/test.sh`
- `./test/test-multi-repo-phase0.sh`
- `./test/test-multi-repo-phase1.sh`
all passed after the separation change.
